# FreeeMarket CMS / admin — environment configuration.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. The CMS is one SHARED app for all shops: the
# merchant connects their own wallet, and that connected address IS their seller
# address. There is no per-shop build — the wallet selects the shop.
#
# When VITE_MARKETPLACE_ADDRESS is unset the app runs in UNCONFIGURED MODE: it
# still renders (so `npm run build` + `npm run preview` show the admin shell),
# but on-chain reads/writes are disabled and a banner explains what to set.
#
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the client by Vite. NEVER put secrets
# here. In particular the merchant's ECIES DECRYPTION PRIVATE KEY (used to read
# shipping addresses, CLAUDE.md §5) must NEVER be committed or placed in env —
# it lives only on the merchant's machine. Run this CMS LOCALLY so plaintext
# addresses + that key never leave your computer.

# Address of the shared Marketplace escrow contract on Gnosis Chain (id 100).
VITE_MARKETPLACE_ADDRESS=

# Ownerless HandleRegistry contract on Gnosis (handle -> seller address). Enables
# the "Storefront handle" card so a merchant can claim their multi-tenant URL
# (freeemarket.eth.limo/<handle>). When unset, that card shows a disabled note.
VITE_HANDLE_REGISTRY=

# Gnosis Chain JSON-RPC endpoint. Default below is the public Gnosis RPC.
VITE_RPC_URL=https://rpc.gnosischain.com

# Swarm Bee node base URL — used for BOTH reads (metadata/images) and WRITES
# (uploading shop/listing JSON + images). Writes REQUIRE a real, writeable Bee
# node, NOT a public gateway. Default is a local node. Get one via Bee or the
# Freedom Browser bundle.
VITE_BEE_URL=http://localhost:1633

# Swarm postage batch ID (the "stamp"). REQUIRED for uploads — Swarm charges for
# storage via postage batches (CLAUDE.md §5). Without it, uploads are disabled
# and the UI shows a warning. Create one with `bee.createPostageBatch(amount,
# depth)` or the Bee API / Swarm dashboard, then paste the 64-hex batch id here.
# This is NOT a secret (it's a storage credit reference), but it is per-node.
VITE_POSTAGE_BATCH_ID=

# SwarmChat ContactRegistry contract address. The CMS uses it to resolve the
# BUYER's published ECIES public key when sending a shipment update / tracking
# code back to the buyer (seller→buyer, CLAUDE.md §5). When UNSET (or the lookup
# returns no key) the tracking-send flow is unconfigured and falls back to a
# stub. NOTE: reading the buyer's shipping ADDRESS does NOT need this — only your
# unlocked ECIES private key. Confirm the registry's exact ABI/selector against
# the deployed SwarmChat registry — centralized in src/lib/contactRegistry.js.
VITE_CONTACT_REGISTRY=

# The merchant's ECIES DECRYPTION PRIVATE KEY is intentionally NOT an env var:
# putting it here would bake it into the client bundle. Instead, unlock it at
# runtime via the "Unlock decryption key" field in the Orders dashboard. It is
# held only in React/sessionStorage state, never persisted to localStorage by
# default, never logged, and never sent anywhere. Run this CMS LOCALLY.

# Optional: comma-separated list of known accepted-token addresses to offer in
# the listing form's token picker (e.g. Gnosis WXDAI + bridged USDC). Each is
# still verified against the on-chain `acceptedTokens` allowlist before use.
VITE_KNOWN_TOKENS=
